|elevation_m =128 |elevation_ft =420 |footnotes = }} 'Patch' (formerly,
'Weedpatch') is an unincorporated community in Kern County,
California. It is located on the railroad southeast of
Bakersfield, at an elevation of 420 feet (128 m).

The place was originally called Weedpatch, but the name was shortened by the
railroad.
